Same-sex relationships in Liechtenstein that are recognised as civil partnerships under British law are known as ‘eingetragene Partnerschaft’, or ’registered partnership’.

^You should [get legal advice](/government/collections/list-of-lawyers) before making any plans.^

##What you need to do

Contact the relevant local authorities in Liechtenstein to find out about local laws, including what documents you’ll need.

There aren’t any British consular facilities to register a same-sex relationship, or get legal documents to prove you’re eligible to enter into a same-sex relationship, in Liechtenstein.
